<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10049b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10049b">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10049b"> 49(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 20,000 horses / 4 mill per year</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On estime que, pendant le xviii<sup>e</sup> si&egrave;cle, la maison Tour et Taxis gagnait chaque jour une vingtaine de mille livres, ce qui faisait par an 4 millions de b&eacute;n&eacute;fice net, quoiqu&apos;elle employ&acirc;t vingt mille hommes et un plus grand nombre de chevaux, car seule elle transportait les voyageurs aussi bien que les d&eacute;p&ecirc;ches. It is estimated that during the 18th century the house of Thurn und Taxis earned about 20,000 pounds a day, which makes for a net profit of 4 million pounds a year, despite the fact that it employed 20,000 men and a greater number of horses, since only Thurn und Taxis transported travellers as well as dispatches.] <small> Eug&egrave;ne Gallois, <a name="EGLP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EGLP"><cite title="source">La Poste</cite></a> (1894) 96</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
